ast.name: facebook
ast.comment: Allows to create requests against the Facebook Graph APIs.

body.text: This library provides the building blocks to do Facebook Graph API requests (http://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/apis/).
## Registering a Facebook app
Before you get started, you will need to create a Facebook app (if you have not done so). Start from here:
* https://developers.facebook.com/apps
Once you've created your Facebook app, expand the `Website with Facebook Login` tab and enter the following url:
* https://www.touchdevelop.com/[userid]/oath
where `[userid]` should be replaced with your TouchDevelop user id. That is the funny word listed under your name in the hub (`/xyz`).
## Authentication
Grab your Facebook Application ID and pass it to the `authentication` action. Do not worry about leaking this id; it is designed to be public.
## Posting to the Facebool wall
A common Facebook activity is to post a message to your wall. This is done through the `post text`, `post message` or `post link` actions.
## Creating requests
You can use the `create request` action to craft more specialized requests against the Facebook Graph API.
The library will append the access token as needed; and will refresh the token if necessary.
Once you have the request object, you can set the additional parameters and send it away!
Authenticates the user with the given application.
Creates a Facebook Graph request with the given path and additional query arguments. Authenticates the user if needed. Returns invalid if authentication failed.
Posts a message to the current user Facebook wall. Requires `publish_stream` scope.
Sends the Facebook Graph request and tries to handle gracefully errors.
Posts the message on the current user Facebook wall. Requires `publish_stream` scope.
Posts the message and the link on the current user Facebook wall. Requires `publish_stream` scope.

eIhBS8O9qLp9uCr5a5hIHaD6.text: The second argument is the permission scope. For example, to post to the users wall, you will need the 'publish_stream' permission.

HRl2t59nEx9ldVXL6lWNJCGS.text: You can read the messages on a user wall by using `feed`. Leave `user id` blank for the current user. Requires `read_stream` permission.

n74UMUfijCn0hC4HWJh3EmR2.text: Facebook returns the elements of the wall page by page. To get the next set of feed element, call `feed next` with the messages. The new message will be added to the collection and `feed next` will return `false` when done.

ic5l57Zi8aCfUh7nQM4phxYC.text: A common Facebook activity is to post messages or photos to your wall. This is done through the `post text`, `post message`, `post link` or `post picture` actions. These actions require the `publish_stream` permission.

exn0thfwlPA4oMYlWibMduFk.text: Let's create a dummy picture to upload...

BHxTIDNDhUDKqcJ7kaGPCdiF.text: Posting the picture to the Facebook wall.

UevcUa2u1wEWBMalJ47EDK0d.text: * `friends` returns the friends from a user. The returned value is a map from each user id to its name.

ZnnqBsAt0HEZOlwTbFjF91Lx.text: * `friend lists` returns the list of friends if any. This feature requires the `read_friendlists` permission. Then you can use the `friend list` action to get the list of users in each list.

GXs2hZZ2vCm2joahNUOLhwZc.text: You can use `post leaderboard score` to create or update the user score for your game. Requires the `publish_actions` permission and the app must be categorized as `game`. See http://developers.facebook.com/docs/howtos/scores/ .

AJPxq3M2u242dqspsZ28OToc.text: You can read the current user score using `score`.

eEa44EvRbFBlpgWDyT1w32s4.text: You can also use `show leaderboards` to push a page with the leaderboards.

SidUuNGDAvi2nl0aLwFnPYpA.text: The library authenticate the user as needed. If you want to explicitely authenticate the user, use `authenticate`:

xEow7C6vWYKiYQzz8FL2NAfF.text: Posts a message to the current user Facebook wall and returns the ID of the generated message if successfull. Leave `user id` blank to use the current user. Requires `publish_stream` scope.

xdVdrRuzBkzqgYygSABJLUb7.text: Most likely the oauth access token is expired

VJSjES0y4c7ew4GjXvnLyExo.text: Posts the message on a Facebook user wall and returns the ID of the generated message if successful. Use `message->to` to specify the `user id` or leave blank to target the current user. Requires `publish_stream` scope.

xZti2D5U9gH6QyXnJ2XD7leM.text: Posts the message and the link on the current user Facebook wall and returns the ID of the generated message if successfull. Leave `user id` blank to use the current user. Requires `publish_stream` scope.

Pj921832dUQ4ejqQAc1zZUJ6.text: Gets the user score for this app. Returns 0 if no score published yet. Use `post leaderboard score` to publish a score.

ojyRAtX9X0objLgDfDHn4bNK.text: Posts the user score to Facebook. Requires the `publish_actions` permission and the app must be categorized as `game`. See http://developers.facebook.com/docs/howtos/scores/ .

kWwVr4GjMmPnfWstu2HTiYVm.text: Downloads the leaderboard scores locally. To display the leaderboards, use `display leaderboards`. Requires the `publish_actions` permission and the app must be categorized as `game`. See http://developers.facebook.com/docs/howtos/scores/ .

EA47etG4TV2VcI8YuLpdrmya.text: Displays the leaderboard scores downloaded by `sync leaderboards`. Must be called within a page.

kc0b24EgddarF7O5n7NKyIRy.text: Posts a picture to the current Facebook user wall and returns the ID of the uploaded photo if successful. `picture name` will be used when saving the picture; `message` is optional. Requires `publish_stream` scope.

xWfjK8VAG7XW4CocvzYDppjE.text: Given a Facebook Graph object ID, returns a link to the corresponding picture. `options` contains a query string of optional requirements. `type=square` for a square image.

HCBaJ0CCbfw4loCAr9Tfa996.text: Gets the list of friends as a map of 'id' to 'name'. Leave `user id` blank to use the current user. Requires the `read_friendlists` permission.

v2AD2uTF6VjeJv2mIHPlu25V.text: Gets the list of friendlists as a map of 'id' to 'name'. Requires the `read_friendlists` permission.

X5Z119xO1gyJYzmUUUvkbLxr.text: Gets the list of friends in the `id` friendlist as a map of 'id' to 'name'.

wxGzZeuZuobMCgE1iFN9B264.text: Clears invites for this user. You MUST call this action in your script when using the `invite friends` action. This allows the library to remove app requests from the user notification list.

xlzpvBtD7NLBb1S4mxfo73HV.text: calling async to avoid blocking for this cleanup operation

q2woknEVJfq7DJxdEkptP8QI.text: Pops a dialog inviting friends to try the app. If `user id` is specified, the user will not have a choice of recipients. See https://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/dialogs/requests/ for more information.

w6bjTU8LuNMNHuA59lLgf2z9.text: Retreives the latest posts on a user wall. Requires the `read_stream` permission.

iiS0RqU2jX3LwSDVJ1242a4k.text: Appends the next set of feed elements and update the `continuation`.

WviqdlhUbEvyRWmjfTUo8S8V.text: Initializes the application information. `scope` is a comma-separated list of permissions used by this application. Both arguments are required.
